memories.content:
A practical plan outlining main medical checks and steps to take during the first month after adopting a pet, with species notes.

- Immediate (24–72 hours): confirm medical records and paperwork; obtain vaccine history, microchip number, spay/neuter status, and recent meds/treatments; arrange a vet visit within the first week, contacting an exotics vet if reptiles/small mammals.

- Initial vet visit (within first week): full physical exam; weight and body condition scoring; review vaccine status and plan; parasite screening and treatment; microchip scan/registration; discuss preventive care;
